{
  "id": "ramp-task-manager",
  "kind": "problem",
  "title": "Progressive Task Manager APIs",
  "difficulty": "hard",
  "timeboxMinutes": 90,
  "concepts": [
    "stateful design",
    "dispatch",
    "sorting",
    "intervals"
  ],
  "prompt": "Suppose an interviewer asks you to build the first slice of a tiny in-memory task-management backend. The system receives a list of operations, and for each operation you return the result as a string.\n\nWrite `taskManager(operations)`. Every operation is a list of strings, and the result should contain one string per operation, in the same order.\n\nThis is a progressive problem. Later levels add users, assignments, completion, and overdue state to the same function. For now, keep the implementation small, but structure it as a clean dispatcher so the next levels have somewhere obvious to go.\n\n**Level 1 operations**\n\n- [\"ADD\", timestamp, name, priority]: create a task and return its new id.\n- [\"GET\", timestamp, task_id]: return `\"name|priority\"` for an existing task, or `\"\"` if the task does not exist.\n\nTasks have an id, name, priority, and creation order. Task ids are assigned as `task_1`, `task_2`, and so on. Numeric fields such as timestamps and priorities are provided as strings.\n\nAt this level, timestamps are included to match the later API shape, but they do not affect behavior yet.",
  "signature": {
    "name": "taskManager",
    "inputs": [
      {
        "name": "operations",
        "type": {
          "type": "array",
          "items": {
            "type": "array",
            "items": {
              "type": "string"
            }
          }
        }
      }
    ],
    "output": {
      "type": "array",
      "items": {
        "type": "string"
      }
    }
  },
  "tests": [
    {
      "name": "add and get",
      "args": [
        [
          [
            "ADD",
            "1",
            "write docs",
            "5"
          ],
          [
            "GET",
            "2",
            "task_1"
          ]
        ]
      ],
      "expected": [
        "task_1",
        "write docs|5"
      ],
      "visibility": "visible"
    },
    {
      "name": "missing get and sequential ids",
      "args": [
        [
          [
            "GET",
            "0",
            "task_1"
          ],
          [
            "ADD",
            "1",
            "alpha",
            "2"
          ],
          [
            "ADD",
            "2",
            "beta",
            "3"
          ],
          [
            "GET",
            "3",
            "task_2"
          ]
        ]
      ],
      "expected": [
        "",
        "task_1",
        "task_2",
        "beta|3"
      ],
      "visibility": "hidden"
    }
  ],
